verbose_text: Alternatively, the reactive B + can be efficiently trapped by HSO 4 - to form the neutral complex Bs, followed by similar trans-to-cis conversion of the amide group (via TSCs) into Cs that may also lead to C + after HSO 4 - elimination, which is kinetically more likely with an overall barrier of 21.9 kcal / mol and may avoid potential side reactions at reactive carbenium center.
